    public class RmiSession
extends UnicastRemoteObject
implements IExceptionListener, ISession, Closeable
    RMI server object for servicing remote ISession requests from an RMI client.

        Returns the first message with the given sequence number or greater or null if none.

      • getMessageFrom

        public IRemoteMessage getMessageFrom(int msgSeqNum,
                                     long timeout)
                              throws RemoteException
        Description copied from interface: ISession
        Returns the first message with the given sequence number or greater.

        If msgSeqNum is 0, the first message that we have will be returned.

        This call blocks until the message is returned or until the given timeout expires. If the timeout expires, it will return null.

        Specified by:
        getMessageFrom in interface ISession
        Parameters:
        msgSeqNum - 0 for first message or else sequence number from where we want to find the next message.
        timeout - Maximum number of milliseconds to wait for a message.
        Returns:
        Message found or null.
        Throws:
        RemoteException - if a communication-related problem occurs

      • getMessagesFrom

        public IRemoteMessage[] getMessagesFrom(int msgSeqNum)
                                 throws RemoteException
        Description copied from interface: ISession
        Returns all messages with the given sequence number or greater.

        If msgSeqNum is 0, all messages in the allowable range are returned.

        This call returns immediately with the requested messages.

        Note:
        This is much more efficient than making multiple getMessageFrom calls if there are many messages waiting to be processed. With this method all messages are returned in a single remote invocation.

        Specified by:
        getMessagesFrom in interface ISession
        Parameters:
        msgSeqNum - 0 for first message or else sequence number from where we want to find the next message.
        Returns:
        Array of messages found - never null but may be empty. The maximum number of messages returned here is governed by server side configuration in order to protect against inadvertent attempts to create a massive return value array.
        Throws:
        RemoteException - if a communication-related problem occurs

      • getMessagesFrom

        public IRemoteMessage[] getMessagesFrom(int msgSeqNum,
                                        long timeout)
                                 throws RemoteException
        Description copied from interface: ISession
        Returns all messages with the given sequence number or greater.

        If msgSeqNum is 0, all messages in range are returned.

        This call blocks until at least one message is available or until the given timeout expires. If the timeout expires, an empty array is returned.

        Note:
        This is much more efficient than making multiple getMessageFrom calls if there are many messages waiting to be processed. With this method all messages are returned in a single remote invocation.

        Specified by:
        getMessagesFrom in interface ISession
        Parameters:
        msgSeqNum - 0 for first message or else sequence number from where we want to find the next message.
        timeout - Maximum number of milliseconds to wait for a message. The maximum number of messages returned here is governed by server side configuration in order to protect against inadvertent attempts to create a massive return value array.
        Returns:
        Array of messages found - never null but may be empty.
        Throws:
        RemoteException - if a communication-related problem occurs
